        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 12 at 3:30PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 328 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Ephesus, or 11 miles
east of Wedowee, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Carrollton, Bowdon, Mount Zion, Ephesus, Roopville, Frolona, John
Tanner State Park, Tyus, Blackjack Mountain, Roosterville, and
Waresville.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
